<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="notes on type locality">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Notes on type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
Nothing is known about the exact places and circumstances of its collecting. The Hedjaz Range is a mountain range located in the Hejazi region, the western part of the country. It is very likely, as in the case of two Saudi Arabian species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acinopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acinopus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Acinopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. brittoni" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="brittoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">A. brittoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wrase &amp; Kataev, 2016 and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. arabicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="arabicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">A. arabicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wrase &amp; Kataev, 2016 (
<bibRefCitation author="Wrase, DW" journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitraege" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="1783 - 1806" refId="B53" refString="Wrase, DW, Kataev, BM, 2016. Four new species of genus Acinopus Dejean, 1821, subgenus Acinopus from southern Iran, from Sinai, and from western Saudi Arabia, and faunistic and taxonomic notes on species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Harpalini, Harpalina). Linzer Biologische Beitraege 48 (2): 1783 - 1806" title="Four new species of genus Acinopus Dejean, 1821, subgenus Acinopus from southern Iran, from Sinai, and from western Saudi Arabia, and faunistic and taxonomic notes on species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Harpalini, Harpalina)." volume="48" year="2016">Wrase and Kataev 2016</bibRefCitation>
), that 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. arabicus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arabicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">P. arabicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lives in higher altitudes where habitats with enough moisture are present.
</paragraph>
